{"word":"ἕξις","slug":"ἕξις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἕξις</b></el> <el>(ἕξις, εως) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἕξω</el>, <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> of <el>ἔχω</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a having, possession</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>(<a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a>) <i>a habit</i> of body, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> <i>a good habit</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a habit of mind</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}